<FIRST>r a AM-DoubleSuicide 1stLd-Writethru a0657 08-24 0240</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Double Suicide, 1st Ld-Writethru, a0657,0242</SECOND>
<HEAD>Teen-agers Throw Themselves from Balcony</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: SUBS 2nd graf to CLARIFY time element.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LAKE BUENA VISTA, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two Ohio teen-agers left a suicide
note in their hotel room, then leaped 12 stories to their deaths
from their balcony at Walt Disney World, authorities said Wednesday.
   Jerry Heitzman, 17, of Tipp City, and Christine Ruetter, 18, of
Kettering, were killed Tuesday when they landed on the roof of the
first-floor restaurant at a Howard Johnson, said Orange County
sheriff's spokeswoman Denise Gainer.
   ``They wrote a note expressing their intention to commit suicide
and jumped together from their 14th-story balcony,'' she said. The
hotel has no 13th floor.
   The contents of the note were not released.
   The teen-agers' parents were unaware they had traveled to
Florida, investigators said. Heitzman's parents were in the Orlando
area late Wednesday, and the woman's parents were expected by
Thursday afternoon, Ms. Gainer said.
   ``The father had reported his son missing. The mother of the
daughter was vacationing when the daughter left, so she was unaware
when the daughter left with Heitzman,'' Ms. Gainer said.
``Apparently they used the daughter's mom's credit card for the
room.''
   The teen-agers, who had known each other for about two months,
drove to Florida in the boy's pickup truck, checked into the hotel
Saturday and were scheduled to check out Wednesday, she said. They
visited both Disney World and the Disney-MGM Studios.
</TEXT>
