<FIRST>r a PM-Self-SacrificingPrincipal CORRECTIVE   08-24 0097</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Self-Sacrificing Principal, CORRECTIVE,0096</SECOND>
<HEAD>Eds: Members who used a0537, PM-Self-Sacrificing Principal, sent
Aug. 16 under a RICHMOND, Mass., dateline, are asked to use the following.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>RICHMOND, Mass. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Associated Press reported erroneously
Aug. 16 that the school system in Richmond once was cited by the
federal government for excellence.
   The state education official who provided the information has
since corrected himself; the school received a state award for
excellence. The information was contained in a story about a high
school principal who was rehired after cutting his own job to save
those of teachers.
