<FIRST>r i PM-China-Flies     08-24 0205</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-China-Flies,0214</SECOND>
<HEAD>Man Kills Flies for Fun and Profit</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Forget about fly swatters. An 81-year-old Beijing
retiree lays traps and kills flies wholesale _ 700,000 over the past
decade.
   Hu Changfu does it for fun and profit, the official Xinhua News
Agency said Wednesday.
   ``When I see the flies flying into the cage, I feel a sense of
happiness,'' it quoted Hu as saying.
   He kills 4,000 a day during the ``fly-killing season'' from April
to October, and gets about one-hundredth of a U.S. cent for each
carcass from the neighborhood sanitary committee.
   Hu's record was 5.6 pounds of flies _ about 102,000 _ in May,
when student pro-democracy protesters jammed the streets and
hampered garbage pickup.
   His method is to put a fly trap resembling a bird cage near the
garbage cans and the public toilet on his lane, and bait it with
hairtail fish, a fly favorite.
   Xinhua recently has displayed special interest in insects.
   It reported Tuesday that Inner Mongolia's capital, Hohhot, was
declared China's first cockroach-free city.
   Senior leader Deng Xiaoping has likened Western liberal ideas to
flies that come in China's open window, but the reports on insect
killing did not appear to have political significance.
</TEXT>
