<SECOND>PM-BRF--Romania-Bomb,0141</SECOND>
<HEAD>Ceausescu Dismisses Rumors About Romanian Atom Bomb</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BELGRADE, Yugoslavia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Romanian President Nicolae Ceausescu
in a published interview dismissed speculation about his country's
nuclear weapon capabilities, but stopped short of denying Romania
has such arms.
   The Yugoslavian weekly Danas raised the issue following months of
rumors that Romania is building nuclear weapons. Speculation
heightened in April when Ceausescu said his country has the
potential to manufacture the arms.
   ``There always are insane people who speculate,'' Danas quoted
Ceausescu as saying. ``I do not even wish to discuss this, to lower
myself to such a level.''
   The weekly also asked the Romanian leader what he does for
recreation, and quoted him as saying he likes watching the U.S.
detective series ``Kojak.'' But, the leader was quoted as saying,
``My hobby is achieving socialism in Romania.''
