<FIRST>u i AM-Israel-Kidnapping 1stLd-Writethru a0435 08-24 0254</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Israel-Kidnapping, 1st Ld-Writethru, a0435,0260</SECOND>
<HEAD>Israeli Kidnapped in West Bank Arab Town</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: LEADS throughout with details, quotes. No pickup</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JERUSALEM (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Masked Palestinians with knives and axes
abducted an Israeli check collector in the occupied West Bank town
of Tulkarem, Israel radio said Thursday.
   Police and troops launched searches in Tulkarem and the
surrounding Arab villages for the missing man, the radio said.
   An army spokeswoman confirmed that an unidentified man had
reported the kidnapping to Tulkarem police on Wednesday night and
that troops were searching but could provide no further details.
   The Israeli, whose name was not given, went to Tulkarem in an
Arab taxi to collect money from a local merchant Wednesday evening,
the radio said.
   Army radio said security forces had not ruled out a criminal
motive in the abduction.
   An army spokeswoman who can not be identified under military
rules told the Associated Press: ``We have a report from local
residents that a person who came to collect checks has been
kidnapped.
   ``The army is carrying out widespread searches and we are
checking information,'' she said.
   The army sealed off the area of Tulkarem on Thursday.
   Israel radio said masked Arab youths wielding knives and axes had
the Arab cab driver take the car down an alleyway, then forced the
Israeli out. They told the driver to wait for the man's return, it
said.
   The driver reported the incident to Israeli police in Tulkarem,
and police forces began combing the town and surrounding villages,
the radio said.
</TEXT>
