<FIRST>r i PM-BRF--France-Drought     08-24 0127</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--France-Drought,0134</SECOND>
<HEAD>Government Orders Aid to Farmers</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PARIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Socialist government has ordered $90 million in
aid for farmers hit by severe drought in western and southern France.
   Farm advocates said the aid was much too small.
   ``It's a beginning,'' Agriculture Minister Henri Nallet said on
French television after announcing the aid package.
   Nallet said it was too soon to estimate how much of this year's
harvest will be lost.
   The National Federation of Farmers' Unions said 300,000 farmers
from Cherbourg to Nice have been hurt by the drought.
   The aid program includes low-interest and zero-interest loans, a
fund for heavily indebted farmers, and a request to the European
Economic Community to let farmers who lost their crops buy European
surpluses at reduced cost.
</TEXT>
