<FIRST>r i PM-Lebanon-Assassination     08-24 0196</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Lebanon-Assassination,0202</SECOND>
<HEAD>Senior Abu Nidal Aide Assassinated Outside Sidon</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SIDON, Lebanon (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Gunmen assassinated a senior aide of
Palestinian terrorist Abu Nidal in an ambush on the northern
outskirts of south Lebanon's provincial capital, riddling him with
15 bullets, police reported.
   He was identified by his nom de guerre of Rabah Abdul-Rahim.
Police said they do not know his real name or his age, but said he
was a senior member of Abu Nidal's Fatah-Revolutionary Council
faction.
   Abdul-Rahim was driving with his bodyguards late Wednesday into
Sidon from Beirut, 25 miles to the north, when gunmen in a black
sedan raked his car with machine gun fire, police said.
   One of his bodyguards, Hisham Saeed, 28, was seriously wounded,
the spokesman added.
   No group claimed responsibility for the assassination.
   Abu Nidal has long been at odds with Palestine Liberation
Organization chairman Yasser Arafat, who has re-established a major
power base in the refugee camps of Ein el-Hilweh and Mieh Mieh in
Sidon.
   Abu Nidal, whose real name is Sabri al-Banna, is high on U.S. and
western European wanted lists for scores of terrorist attacks,
including the December 1985 attacks on Rome and Vienna airports.
</TEXT>
