<FIRST>r a PM-Horse'sHead     08-24 0209</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Horse's Head,0214</SECOND>
<HEAD>Man Leaves Horse's Head at Federal Building</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: Note contents.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ATLANTA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Authorities say they don't know why a man dumped a
severed horse's head in front of a federal court building, but the
man accused in the act is behind bars.
   FBI agents arrested Claude L. Philibert, 46, of Felton, on
Wednesday evening after Cobb County police stopped his car in
Marietta a few hours after the dumping at the Richard B. Russell
Federal Building in downtown Atlanta.
   FBI spokesman Diader H. Rosario said Philibert was to be
arraigned this morning on charges of threatening a federal officer.
   In the Mario Puzo book and movie ``The Godfather,'' the Mafia
leaves a horse's head in a movie producer's bed as a threat.
   But Rosario said, ``We don't know why he might have done this.''
   Witnesses told authorities they saw a man drive a black Chrysler
New Yorker onto the sidewalk to the federal building's front door
and, appearing highly agitated, take a plastic bag from the car's
trunk Wednesday afternoon.
   As he approached the front door, witnesses said, the bag ripped
and he dropped it, exposing the horse's head. The witnesses also
said the man was wearing an empty gun holster on his hip.
</TEXT>
