<HEAD>Community College to Drop Requirements that Irked County Board</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: Note contents.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HEMPSTEAD, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Visits to gay bars and interviews with
prostitutes have been dropped from a community college's sexuality
course after the county Board of Supervisors balked at approving the
school's budget.
   Officials at Nassau Community College agreed Wednesday to drop
the material, said Ed Ward, executive assistant to Hempstead's
