<FIRST>r a PM-BRF--ChildRescued     08-24 0140</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Child Rescued,0142</SECOND>
<HEAD>Child Freed From Water Main</HEAD>
<HEAD>LaserPhoto SA1</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN ANTONIO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 6-year-old boy who became trapped in an
abandoned water main for 30 minutes after climbing in on a dare was
freed when paramedics poured dishwashing liquid on his body to make
him slippery enough to pull out.
   Bobby Pitterman was taken to a hospital with minor injuries after
the ordeal Wednesday night. The pipe in which he got stuck was about
1 foot in diameter and about 3 feet deep.
   ``We got him to relax and as soon as we got him to relax enough
we got him to slide out'' by lubricating his body with the
dishwashing liquid, paramedic David Willis said.
   Willis said if the soap had not worked they would have had to dig
and break the pipe to free him.
</TEXT>
