<FIRST>r a PM-DoubleSuicide     08-24 0245</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Double Suicide,0250</SECOND>
<HEAD>Teen-agers Leap From Balcony At Disney World</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: Retransmitting to correct cycle designator.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LAKE BUENA VISTA, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two teen-agers who had known each
other about two months visited Walt Disney World and the Disney-MGM
Studios, then left a note and leaped to their deaths from a 14th
floor balcony, officials said.
   Jerry Heitzman, 17, of Tipp City, Ohio, and Christine Reutter,
18, of Kettering, Ohio, were killed late Tuesday when they hit the
roof of the first-floor restaurant at the Howard Johnson at Walt
Disney Village, said Orange County sheriff's spokeswoman Denise
Gainer.
   ``They each left a suicide note that said they cared very deeply
for one another, and that they wanted to live with each other for
eternity,'' sheriff's spokesman Jim Solomons said.
   ``Since he was younger and she was to go into the Air Force in
November, they didn't feel they could be together,'' said Andrea
Carter, a friend of the Reutter family.
   Ms. Reutter tried to kill herself with an overdose of pills
nearly two years ago, said Megan Fitzgerald, a friend of Ms.
Reutter, the Dayton (Ohio) Daily News reported today.
   The pair's parents were unaware that they had traveled to
Florida, investigators learned.
   The teen-agers, who had known each other for about two months,
drove to Florida in Heitzman's pickup, checked into the hotel
Saturday and were scheduled to check out Wednesday, Ms. Gainer said.
They visited both Disney World and the Disney-MGM Studios.
</TEXT>
