<FIRST>r w PM-HighwayCost     08-24 0077</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Highway Cost,70</SECOND>
<HEAD>Highway Construction Costs Decline 3 Percent</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Highway construction costs decreased 3 percent
in the second quarter of 1989, the Federal Highway Administration
announced today.
   The overall reduction resulted from significant decreases in
prices for reinforcing steel, structural concrete, structural steel
and excvation, the agency said.
   The result lowered the agency's composite index for highway
construction costs to 176.7 percent of the 1977 average cost figure
it uses as its base.
