<FIRST>r w AM-EggProduction     08-24 0096</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Egg Production,90</SECOND>
<HEAD>Egg Production Continues To Decline</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Egg production continues to drop, meaning
higher prices for consumers, an Agriculture Department report showed
Thursday.
   July production was estimated at 5.63 billion eggs, down 2
percent from a year earlier, the report said. Production included
4.89 billion eggs for the table and 738 million for hatching.
   As of Aug. 1, the laying flock was about 264.2 million birds,
down 2 percent from a year ago.
   However, production averaged 68.1 eggs per 100 birds, virtually
the same as a year earlier, the report said.
</TEXT>
