<SECOND>PM-Treasury Auction,0105</SECOND>
<HEAD>Yields Fall on 5-Year Treasury Notes</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Yields on 5-year Treasury notes fell in
Wednesday's auction to the lowest level in two and a half years.
   The average yield was 8.26 percent, down from 8.72 percent at the
last comparable auction on May 25, 1989.
   It was the lowest rate since 5-year notes averaged 6.73 percent
on Feb. 25, 1987. The notes will carry a coupon interest rate of 8\
percent with each $10,000 in face value selling for $9,989.30.
   A total of $7.8 billion in notes were sold out of bids totaling
$26.15 billion.
</TEXT>
