<FIRST>r f BC-Earns-Sony     08-24 0166</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Earns-Sony,0174</SECOND>
<HEAD>Sony Earnings Up 44.2 Percent In Quarter</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Sony Corp.'s profit rose 44.2 percent in its first
fiscal quarter on a 23.4 percent gain in sales, the company said
Thursday.
   Profit for Sony and its consolidated subsidiaries rose to 23.2
billion yen in the quarter ended June 30, or $166 million, from 16.1
billion yen in the same period a year earlier. Sales rose to 571.8
billion yen, or $4.08 billion, from 463.6 billion yen a year earlier.
   Sales to the United States rose 28.2 percent, while sales inside
Japan rose 17.2 percent, the company said.
   The company also projected its results for the full fiscal year,
which ends next April 30. It predicted a 24 percent rise in profit
to 90 billion yen, or $643 million, and sales of 2.45 trillion yen,
or $17.5 billion.
   All dollar equivalents have been obtained by using an exchange
rate of 140 yen to the dollar. The calculation was not done by the
company.
</TEXT>
