<HEAD>Production Goes Up This Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce
210,102 cars and light trucks this week, up from last week's
201,195, Ward's Automotive Reports said Thursday.
   This week's production is higher than the same week a year ago,
in which 125,606 cars and light trucks were produced, the trade
journal said.
   U.S. automakers were scheduled to make 131,458 cars this week,
compared with 125,544 a week ago and 125,606 in the same week in
1988.
   Light truck production for the week was scheduled at 78,644,
compared with last week's 75,651 and last year's 75,195.
   Canadian automakers were to build 19,733 cars this week, up from
17,656 a week ago and from last year's 14,816.
   Canadian light truck production was scheduled at 17,641, compared
with 19,837 a week ago and 18,245 in the same week last year.
