<FIRST>r f BC-Lorillard-Tisch     08-24 0210</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Lorillard-Tisch,0218</SECOND>
<HEAD>Andrew Tisch To Head Tobacco Concern</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Andrew Tisch on Thursday was named chairman and
chief executive officer of Lorillard Inc., the tobacco subisdiary of
Loews Corp., which is run by his billionaire family.
   Tisch, 40, will relinquish his post as president of Bulova Corp.,
another Tisch family holding, but will remain a director of the
watch concern.
   Headquartered in New York, Lorillard makes Kent, Newport, and
True brands of cigarettes, along with other cigarette, cigar and
chewing tobacco products. The company has annual revenue of about
$1.8 billion.
   Tisch is the son of Laurence Tisch, who, along with his brother,
former U.S. Postmaster General Preston Robert, serve as co-CEOs of
Loews Corp. Loews has a 25 percent stake in CBS and also controls
Loews Hotels, CNA Financial and Bulova, among other investments.
   Andrew Tisch joined Lorillard in 1971 in the marketing
department. He joined Loews as a director of financial planning in
the late 1970s and was appointed president of Bulova in 1981. In
1985, he was elected to the Loews board and named vice president of
strategic planning.
   J. Robert Ave, who has served as president and CEO of Lorillard
for the past four years, will continue in the role of president.
</TEXT>
