<TEXT>
   The stock market surged ahead today, surpassing a
record high for the Dow Jones industrial average that had stood for
two years.
   With today's session, the Dow became the last of the widely
recognized market indicators to recover all the ground it lost in
the crash of 1987.
   Analysts said the market benefited from a downturn in interest
