<FILEID>AP-NR-08-24-89 0039EDT</FILEID>
<FIRST>r f BC-AmericanFamilyStation     08-24 0096</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-American Family Station,0100</SECOND>
<DATELINE>COLUMBUS, Ga. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   American Family Corp. announced Wednesday
that its American Family Broadcast Group Inc. subsidiary reached an
agreement in principle to sell television station KTIV-TV of Sioux
City, Iowa, to Quincy Newspapers, Inc., of Quincy, Ill.
   Terms of the deal were not disclosed. American Family bought the
station in 1980.
   The cash sale is expected to be completed this year after
approval by the Federal Communications Commission.
   American Family Corp. is a diversified, international holding
company. Through its AFLAC subsidiary it is a leading underwriter of
supplemental health insurance.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
